description: This table presents the results of a comparison study between eleven different methods for conditional density estimation. The performance metric used is the Kolmogorov-Smirnov (KS) distance between the estimated and true conditional cumulative distribution functions (CDFs). The mean and standard deviation of the KS distance are reported for each method, averaged over ten repetitions, each with a different random seed. The best-performing method for each dataset is highlighted in red, while the second-best method is shown in bold black.

description: This table presents the performance comparison of several conditional density estimation methods.
